Resources

     * [http://www.lexaloffle.com/pico-8.php?page=manual]Official Manual -
       Placeholder dump of pico-8.txt! (Proper manual coming soon).
     * [http://neko250.github.io/pico8-api/]Cheat Sheet - by
       [https://neko250.github.io/]Neko250. Based on the official manual,
       with edits where found appropriate.
     * [http://sectordub.itch.io/pico-8-fanzine-1]PicoZine #1,
       [http://sectordub.itch.io/pico-8-fanzine-2]#2,
       [http://sectordub.itch.io/pico-8-fanzine-3]#3 and
       [https://sectordub.itch.io/-pico-8-zine-4]#4 - PICO-8 Zine is a
       48-page fanzine made by and for PICO-8 users.
     * [https://gist.github.com/josefnpat/bfe4aaa5bbb44f572cd0]Going from
       Lua 5.2 to PICO-8's Lua - This document is here to help folks with
       a proficiency in Lua understand the limitations and discrepencies
       between Lua and PICO-8's Lua.
     * [https://ztiromoritz.github.io/pico-8-spick/]Cheat Sheet
       (printable) - A reduced cheat sheet in a printable format. German
       and Englisch version available.
     * [https://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?tid=28207]Cheat Sheet (wallpaper)
       - An enhancement of the printable cheat sheet for use as a desktop
       wallpaper.

Tutorials

     * [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLjZAika8vyZkyOjoCp0EbHeIFZ8
       MLlhvg]Music Tracker Tutorial Series - Making audio with PICO-8.
     * [https://youtu.be/ZuaLuMhwcc8]Tron Lightcycle game from scratch - A
       quick introduction to PICO-8 writing a game from scratch.
     * [https://ztiromoritz.github.io/pico-8-shooter/]A PICO-8
       Spaceshooter in 16 GIFs - Screencaptures of writing a Spaceshooter
       game step by step.
     * [https://github.com/seleb/PICO-8-Token-Optimizations]Token
       optimization - tips&tricks for saving tokens.
     * [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?tid=3726]Tweetjam, BBS thread -
       cards which code fits in a tweet (really useful to learn some fun
       techniques).
     * [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?search=sample+code]Sample code on
       the BBS - the search is not 100% accurate, but some of those cards
       features some nice tricks you can re-use in your future code.

Tools

     * [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?tid=2462]Sprite Editor - External
       sprite editor compatible with Pico-8 and PicoLove.
     * [https://github.com/briacp/pico2png]pico2png - Spritesheet
       extraction written in perl.
     * [https://www.reddit.com/r/pico8/comments/3jhmni/spritesheets_and_to
       ols_for_the_pico8_palette/]Spritesheets and tools for the PICO-8
       Palette - Compilation of works assest and tools using the PICO-8
       palette.
     * [https://github.com/josefnpat/pico8utils]Pico8Utils - Compilation
       of lua scripts based on the unix philosophy for working with .p8
       files.
     * [https://github.com/dansanderson/picotool]picotool - Tools and
       Python libraries for manipulating Pico-8 game files.
     * [https://github.com/franciscod/p8dl]p8dl - Carts Downloader -
       Python - Downloads cartridges into the correct folder (looks at
       your config.txt).
     * [https://github.com/kikookoubis/pico-8-carts-bash-downloader]Pico-8
       Carts Downloader - Bash - Downloads cartridge from the BBS (single
       cart, whole index or dump your favourited entries) & rename them
       according to their metadata.
     * [https://github.com/benwiley4000/pico8-responsive-webplayer-transfo
       rm]p8 responsive webplayer transform - Python script that makes
       your HTML export page responsive.
     * [http://www.romanzolotarev.com/pico-8-color-palette/]Color Palette
       - Hex and RGB colors codes for web.
     * [https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B97Um39fHXlcWUFRZlBqUndhbXM/view]
       PICO-8 font - by
       [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?uid=11704]RhythmLynx.
     * [https://github.com/jozanza/pico-test]pico-test - PICO-8 testing
       framework.
     * [https://github.com/clowerweb/Lib-Pico8]Lib-Pico8 - A Pico-8
       library of useful common functions.
     * [https://github.com/adamscott/pico8-missing-builtins]pico8-missing-
       builtins - Provides Lua built-in functions to pico8.
     * [https://github.com/movAX13h/P8Coder]P8Coder - A programming tool
       that replaces the lua code in pico-8 cartridges (p8) with the code
       you write in P8Coder.
     * [https://github.com/outkine/pico-kit]Pico-Kit - An opinionated
       collection of Pico-8 helpers that make it easier to get going. Adds
       OOP, better debugging, and physics.
     * [https://github.com/torch2424/picoDeploy]picoDeploy - Deploy Pico-8
       carts as standalone applications on desktop (Electron) and mobile
       (Ionic).
     * [https://github.com/TeamNoComplyGames/pico8Grunt]pico8Grunt - A
       build system for pico8 games, using gruntjs.
     * [https://github.com/JoebRogers/PICO-EC]PICO-EC - A tiny
       scene-entity-component library created for the PICO-8 fantasty
       console.
     * [https://github.com/JoebRogers/PICO-Tween]PICO-Tween - A small
       library of tweening/easing functions for use in the PICO-8 fantasy
       console, inspired by Robert Penner's easing functions.
     * [https://github.com/jozanza/p8]p8 - A dependency manager and build
       tool. Lets you share code/sprites, require() dependencies, and
       auto-reload carts on save. Works with any external code editor and
       supports [https://moonscript.org/]MoonScript.

Text Editors Language Support

     * Visual Studio Code:
       [https://github.com/nathanchere/vscode-pico8]vscode-pico8
     * Atom: [https://atom.io/packages/language-pico8]language-pico8
     * Sublime: [https://packagecontrol.io/packages/PICO-8]Sublime PICO-8
       - PICO-8 plugin for the Sublime Text editor (color scheme, font,
       build system, code completion, snippets...).
     * Vim: [https://github.com/justinj/vim-pico8-syntax]vim-pico8-syntax

Programming Fonts

   You might be interested to install
   [https://github.com/juanitogan/p8-programming-fonts]pico-8 programming
   fonts they support the pico-8 custom characters as well as various
   fonts (bitmap and regular anti-aliased fonts). Check the
   [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?tid=28975]BBS thread here.

   How to install the font(s):
     * Linux: copy the files on ~/.fonts and sudo fc-cache -f -v
     * Windows: copy the files on c:/windows/fonts/

Hacks - undocumented PICO-8 features

     * [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?tid=3549]Mouse - How to retrieve
       mouse coordinates (with demo).
     * [https://github.com/dppc/p8keyboard.js]p8keyboard.js - Javascript
       "keyboard adapter" for the Pico-8. Send ASCII characters to a
       Pico-8 program running in a browser.
     * [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?tid=3561]SFX Modifications - Four
       effects that can only be applied by modifying memory (with demo).
     * [http://www.lexaloffle.com/bbs/?pid=10719#p10719]Tracker
       State/Audio Memory Locations - How to access and modify audio data
       as it is playing.

Hardware

     * [https://getchip.com/pages/pocketchip]PocketC.H.I.P - A portable
       mini-computer, a game console, a portable synthesizer and a Linux
       field terminal with PICO-8 pre-installed.

Articles & Posts

     * [http://www.indieretronews.com/2015/10/pico-8-8-bit-fantasy-console
       -from.html]Indie Retro News - A great introduction to PICO-8 by
       [https://twitter.com/ABrugsch]@ABrugsch.
     * [http://blog.jvscott.net/post/128051478244/clear-code]Clear Code -
       3 part series on how to write better pico-8 code.

Podcasts

     * [http://pico.electrobureau.com/]pico chat - A bite-sized podcast
       about Pico-8 and other tiny games.

Talks

     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AmMYWD2Zbso]Sharing the love -
       Making games with PICO-8. linux conf au 2017 - Hobart, Australia

Clones

     * [https://nesbox.itch.io/tic]TIC-80 by Nesbox - Tiny Computer,
       available on HTML 5, Windows, Linux 32/64bit, Android & MacOSX
     * [https://github.com/gamax92/picolove]PicoLove - Pico-8
       Reimplementation in LÖVE.
     * [https://github.com/RamiLego4Game/LIKO-12]LIKO-12 - An open source
       fantasy computer made using LÖVE with 96kb RAM.
     * [https://github.com/Gigoteur/PX8]PX8 - Open Source Fantasy Console
       (128x128 pixels) in Rust (with Python/LUA code support).

